---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MathTiers from '../../components/MathTiers.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5">
    <div class="pt-10 pb-4">
      <a href="/samples" class="label hover:underline">&larr; Panel samples</a>
      <div class="part-kicker mt-4">Option C</div>
      <h1 class="part-title">Persistent Math Rail</h1>
      <p class="prose-manual max-w-2xl">
        A permanent rail beside the text always shows Tier 1; the reader deepens it in place.
        Most &ldquo;engineering manual&rdquo; in feel — maths is a constant companion, not a
        thing you summon. On mobile the rail drops below the prose.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="py-6 border-t border-[var(--color-rule)]">
      <div class="rail-grid">
        <div class="rail-text">
          <div class="label mb-2">Section 02</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-4">The Traction Budget</h3>
          <div class="prose-manual">
            <p>
              At the limit you get <strong>one</strong> of: 100% throttle, 100% brake, or 100%
              lean. They share a single budget of grip — brake at 70% and you can still lean at
              70%, because the demands add as a vector, not a sum.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3">
              Cross the limit and the tyre lets go. The rail beside this text carries the exact
              model, which you can deepen one tier at a time as far as you care to go.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3">
              Because the rail is always present, equations and prose stay in lock-step — useful
              when nearly every claim has a formula behind it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="rail">
          <div class="rail-head">
            <span class="label"><span class="section-num">&sum;</span>&nbsp;The Maths</span>
          </div>
          <div class="rail-body">
            <MathTiers />
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .rail-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 380px; gap: 2.5rem; align-items: start; }
    .rail-text { max-width: 38rem; }
    .rail {
      position: sticky; top: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-rule); background: var(--color-card);
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px -22px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
    }
    .rail-head { padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule); }
    .rail-body { padding: 0.7rem 0.95rem 1rem; max-height: 78vh; overflow-y: auto; }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .rail-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .rail { position: static; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
